{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783560568,"nonce":"9juNveklMwVrb40/1dbIYm9z4yU=","title":"A column-listed view/CTE body whose own `ORDER BY` (or `GROUP BY`/`HAVING`)","message":"references a **projection alias** re-renders as invalid SQL, because a column\nlist suppresses the projection's `AS \u003calias\u003e` while the clause still references it.\n\nReproduces on a plain view (no CTE):\n\n    CREATE VIEW v (n) AS SELECT 1 AS total ORDER BY total\n\nlowers, then re-renders as:\n\n    CREATE VIEW \"public\".\"v\" (\"n\") AS SELECT 1 ORDER BY \"total\"\n\n— `\"total\"` is undefined, so the DDL is invalid.\n\nRoot cause: for a column-listed body the declared list authoritatively renames\nthe projection's output (to `n`), and the renderer suppresses the projection's\nown `AS` alias (`view_render.rs::render_select`, `alias_projections = false`).\nThe body-local `ORDER BY total` term is lowered/kept as `total`, which no longer\nresolves — the model conflates a projection's *internal* alias with its\n*view-output* name.\n\nPre-existing since PR #91 (2.0); surfaced by Codex during PR 2.0c (CTEs), which\nshares the same `render_select` path. Deferred out of 2.0c (the CTE\nmodel/reverse-parser slice) per maintainer decision.\n\nA correct fix decouples a projection's internal alias from its view-output name\n(store both; emit the internal `AS` alias when a body-local clause references it),\nor resolves names — related to the epic's flagged name-resolution risk\n(`diff.rs` exact-PartialEq needs view-output type/name inference). A cheaper\ninterim option is to reject this shape at lower/render time rather than emit\ninvalid SQL, but a precise reject also needs to know which order terms reference\nsuppressed aliases vs. base columns (name resolution again).\n\nScope: `crates/squealy/src/view_render.rs` (render_select alias suppression),\n`crates/squealy-parse/src/lower.rs` (projection output-name derivation), and the\n`ViewQueryModel`/`ProjectionItem` model shape.","files":null}]}